The paper discusses efficient implementation of linear and nonlinear filters in image processing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The use of shiftable kernels to exploit redundancy in filtering operations suggests a focus on optimization and algorithm design, which could also fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
